# HireIQ — AI-Powered Recruitment Platform

> Automate resume screening, candidate matching, and interview scheduling in one unified platform.

---

## What is HireIQ?

HireIQ is a production-grade web application that helps recruiters manage end-to-end hiring — from posting job descriptions to scheduling Google Meet interviews — with AI doing the heavy lifting on resume evaluation.

A recruiter can upload multiple resumes, select a job description, and instantly get AI-generated match scores, skill gap analysis, and hiring recommendations for every candidate.

---

## Features

### 🤖 AI Resume Matching
Upload one or multiple resumes and evaluate them against any Job Description. The AI extracts candidate info, identifies matching and missing skills, assigns a match score, and gives a hire/no-hire recommendation.

### 📋 Job Description Management
Create and manage multiple open positions. Each JD has its own status (Open / On Hold / Closed), can be assigned to a team member, and is visible to managers via the dashboard.

### 🔄 Candidate Re-Evaluation
Evaluate the same candidate against a different role. Previous scores are stored — the profile always shows the latest result, with full evaluation history accessible in the candidate view.

### 📊 Pipeline Status Tracking
Move candidates through a 7-stage hiring pipeline with optional comments on every status change:

| Status | Meaning |
|---|---|
| 🔵 New | Evaluated, pending review |
| 🟣 Reviewed | Recruiter has reviewed the AI output |
| 🟡 Shortlisted | Moving forward |
| 🔵 Interview Scheduled | Interview booked |
| 🔴 Rejected | Not proceeding |
| 🟢 Hired | Successfully hired |
| ⚫ Archived | Closed out |

### 📅 Interview Scheduling
Schedule, reschedule, or cancel interviews with Google Meet integration. Meeting links are auto-generated and accessible directly from the candidate profile. Past and cancelled interviews are preserved for reference.

### ⚡ Bulk Status Update
Multi-select candidates and update their status in one action — useful for archiving or rejecting all remaining candidates after a position is filled.

### 📁 Resume Viewer
View the original uploaded resume in-app without downloading or switching tools.

### 📤 Export to Excel
Export candidate lists with scores, statuses, and parsed details to `.xlsx` for reporting or offline use.

### 📈 Dashboard
Real-time overview of all positions and candidates. Filter by position to review progress on a specific role. Designed for both recruiter workflow and manager oversight.

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | React (hosted on Vercel) |
| Backend | Python + FastAPI (hosted on Render) |
| Database & Auth | Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth) |
| File Storage | AWS S3 |
| Video Interviews | Google Meet API |

---

## Architecture Overview

```
User (Browser)
     │
     ▼
React Frontend  ──────────────────►  FastAPI Backend
(Vercel)                              (Render)
                                           │
                        ┌──────────────────┼──────────────────┐
                        ▼                  ▼                  ▼
                   Supabase DB          AWS S3           Google Meet API
                (data + auth)      (resume files)     (interview links)
```

The React frontend communicates with the FastAPI backend via REST. The backend handles all business logic, AI processing, file management (S3), and third-party integrations.

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.11+
- Node.js 18+
- Supabase project
- AWS S3 bucket
- Google Meet API credentials

### Backend Setup

```bash
git clone https://github.com/egrnoorfatima-max/AI-Projects/tree/main/backend.git
cd hireiq/backend

python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

pip install -r requirements.txt

cp .env.example .env
# Fill in your environment variables

uvicorn main:app --reload
```

### Frontend Setup

```bash
cd hireiq/frontend

npm install

cp .env.example .env.local
# Add your API base URL

npm run dev
```

### Environment Variables

**Backend `.env`**
```
GROQ_API_KEY=
DATABASE_URL=
SECRET_KEY=
ADMIN_EMAIL=
ADMIN_PASSWORD=
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_REGION=
S3_BUCKET_NAME=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=
```

**Frontend `.env.local`**
```
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
```

